e of him in later years, and because of his genetic alterations, he aged very slowly. I knew he would allow me to keep an eye on you two when you weren't at school." He explained with a laugh. "He is a very smart penguin. I'm glad he chose to help out. I don't think things would have worked out nearly as well without him."</em></div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExpendableClone" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExpendableClone">Expendable Clone</a>: Double subverted. After a while and thanks to her new teacher's teachings, Rei stops seeing herself as expendable. However, because she did not want to die, she <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">replaced herself with other Rei clone during a battle. Rei III accepted to sacrifice herself so that Rei II kept living.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FakingTheDead" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FakingTheDead">Faking the Dead</a>: Ritsuko, Maya and Rei devise a complicated plot <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">involving one of the clones of Rei</span> to trick <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Gendo</span> into believing that someone who stood in the way is dead.</li><li> <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Fanon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Fanon">Fanon</a>:<ul><li> Rei I, II and III have NOT different souls. Rei II and III were NOT different persons.</li><li> Besides Shinji and Asuka, more humans may return from Instrumentality.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FieryRedhead" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FieryRedhead">Fiery Redhead</a>: Asuka's personality mellows down a bit after the first chapters but she 